    "Related WorkVisual Grounding.Visual grounding links textual descriptions to image regions and is addressed in both supervised and zero-shot settings.",
    "Early methods fine-tuned CNNbased detectors in two-stage (Hong et al. 2022) or one-stage frameworks (Yu et al.",
    "2018; Yang et al. 2020), achieving strong closed-set performance but limited open-set flexibility.",
    "The introduction of Vision Transformers (ViTs) (Dosovitskiy et al. 2021) enabled fully transformer-based models like TransVG (Deng et al.",
    "2022), which improve visual-language alignment."
